Different Ways to Access Linux
------------------------------

Local Login:
----------
-Direct access to the Linux system using keyboard and monitor.
Remote Login:
-------------
-Access Linux from another system over a network.
  Common tools:
  ------------
  SSH
  Telnet (not secure)
  VNC

Root in Linux
-------------

Root Account:
-------------
-Root is a superuser account in Linux.
-It has all administrative privileges.
Can:
    Install software
    Modify system files
    Create and delete users

Root Directory:
---------------
-Root directory is the top-most directory in Linux.
-Represented by:
  /
-All other directories are located under the root directory.

Root Home Directory:
--------------------
-Home directory of the root user.
-Represented by:
  /root
-Different from normal usersâ€™ home directories (/home/username).

Quick Comparison:
----------------
|--------------------|--------------------------|
| Term               | Description              |
|--------------------|--------------------------|
| Root Account       | Superuser with all rights|
| Root Directory     | / (top-most directory)   |
| Root Home Directory| /root                    |
|--------------------|--------------------------|

















